# ALLOWLIST: exclude the entire build context, then re-include exactly what
# the Dockerfile COPYs. Anything new in the webroot (secrets, configs, the git
# checkout -- whatever CHECKOUT_DIR is named) is excluded BY DEFAULT instead
# of needing to be remembered here. On the server the context is the assembled
# webroot, which also holds .env (tunnel token) and config.webswr; neither
# belongs anywhere near the docker daemon.
#
# GOTCHA: keep the exclusion a single `*` (NOT `**`, which would also strip
# the re-included directories' contents), and every new COPY line added to the
# Dockerfile needs a matching `!` line below or the build can't find the file.
*
!index.html
!nginx.conf
!css
!js
